      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is a significant difference in impact between a random user's mistake and a deliberate attack from a major political figure. When high-level actors weaponize \"fake news,\" they leverage institutional power to erode public trust in legitimate journalism itself. This deliberate labeling is far more damaging because it attacks the *process* of information gathering, not just a single piece of content. Therefore, the intentional, high-level deployment of the term is arguably the greater threat to democratic discourse.",
